main event: Radar observed a fast moving star-like object at 2000 hrs, estimated speed 2500 mph, altitude 30,000 ft, observed for 9 min, then disappeared.
interesting points: The object was first perceived as a pinpoint of light when viewed with binoculars., The object was visible for a total of 9 minutes before gradually disappearing., There was no air traffic sighted during the observation., The sighting was reported by military personnel., The conditions during the observation were described as a clear night with unlimited ceiling and cumulus clouds.
